# Database Configuration
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/air1

# LinkedIn Authentication (Required for authenticated scraping)
# Get your li_at cookie value from LinkedIn while logged in
LINKEDIN_SID=your_linkedin_li_at_cookie_value

# Email Service (Resend)
RESEND_API_KEY=your_resend_api_key

# Proxy Configuration (Optional - for IP rotation)
# Uncomment and configure these to enable proxy rotation for LinkedIn scraping
# This is useful to avoid rate limits and protect your personal LinkedIn account

# PROXY_SERVER=http://proxy.example.com:8080
# Format options:
#   - HTTP: http://proxy.example.com:8080
#   - HTTPS: https://proxy.example.com:8080
#   - SOCKS5: socks5://proxy.example.com:1080

# PROXY_USERNAME=your_proxy_username
# PROXY_PASSWORD=your_proxy_password

# Proxy Service Recommendations:
# - Bright Data (formerly Luminati): https://brightdata.com (residential proxies)
# - SmartProxy: https://smartproxy.com (affordable residential proxies)
# - ScraperAPI: https://scraperapi.com (managed scraping with built-in proxy rotation)
# - Oxylabs: https://oxylabs.io (enterprise-grade proxies)
#
# Most services offer free trials. For production use, residential proxies
# are recommended as they're less likely to be blocked by LinkedIn.

# Usage Examples:
#
# 1. With authentication + proxy:
#    Set LINKEDIN_SID, PROXY_SERVER, PROXY_USERNAME, PROXY_PASSWORD
#    Call: service.scrape_company_leads(..., use_proxy=True)
#
# 2. Without authentication + proxy:
#    Set PROXY_SERVER, PROXY_USERNAME, PROXY_PASSWORD (no LINKEDIN_SID needed)
#    Initialize: Service(use_auth=False)
#    Call: service.scrape_company_leads(..., use_proxy=True)
#
# 3. With authentication, no proxy (default, uses your IP):
#    Set LINKEDIN_SID only
#    Call: service.scrape_company_leads(...)
